snippet.textDisplay:
If someone has a seizure lasting 30 minutes once per week, a device predicting if they would have a seizure in the next hour would be over 99% accurate if it always answered NO.

I made up the frequency and duration of the seizures, but they seem realistic to me and result in a nice accuracy number. It's to illustrate how accuracy can be deceptive. On the other hand, if someone wanted to predict 100 % of upcoming seizures, a similar device always answering YES would achieve that.
